title._content: This 50-Year-Old Popcorn Stand Is a Fixture in the Community of New Ulm, Minnesota...

description._content: Original Caption: This 50-Year-Old Popcorn Stand Is a Fixture in the Community of New Ulm, Minnesota. Each Spring and Summer It Is Located on Center Street. The Town Was Founded in 1854 by a Group of German Immigrants. It Is Still Predominately a Farming Community Although It Owes Its Growth Since 1950 to Manufacturing Companies That Have Moved In. in the 1960's the Business District Had Vacant Stores and Needed Refurbishing. with Community Effort the Business District Was Revitalized.
